4,"I picked up 3 tortas and 3 churros to-go after a day at Erikson Institute, just down the block. 4 pm on a Friday was a good time to come as there was only one person in line. Counter person and host were friendly and efficient. 

The waiting area is awkwardly placed by the door, so I had to keep moving while guests came in and squeezed past me into the dining area, but I didn&apos;t have to wait too long. 

$48 for my tortas take-away, without sides, is steep so I doubt I&apos;d return, unless it&apos;s a special occasion, but I&apos;m guessing $12-$13 a sandwich is the going rate in the city for a fresh, handmade sandwich. Too steep for me though, especially with no sides, as my teen eats a lot and one sandwich wasn&apos;t enough. My family enjoyed their sandwiches though. My son ate two tortas and my husband ate one. I&apos;m gluten-free and vegetarian, so I didn&apos;t order anything for myself. 

Xoco is a cool and unique place for a quick meal. It&apos;s out of my regular budget, but if you can afford it, I&apos;d recommend a visit."
