5,"Doesn&apos;t look like much when you pass this place maybe because you have so many cool restaurants near by or next to it. But if you don&apos;t want to try anything sophisticated and like tacos, this is the place you need to go to when you&apos;re in this neighborhood. I live in this neighborhood and always keep trying new restaurants or places to hangout around. 

On a Saturday night, if you try to get into any restaurant here, you will find a long waiting to get a table. While we were bar hopping in this area, we wanted to grab something quick to eat and didn&apos;t want to spend too much time in long queues to get a table, we found this place and it looked like we can get food quickly here which was true as their service was pretty fast.

While looking at the menu the manager showed us couple of good vegetarian options which we ordered including one vegetarian taco plate which had like four tacos in it and a vegetarian eggplant sandwich sandwich which was so good compared to any other place I have tried earlier. We also got their special margaritas and loved it too. Two of my friends eat chicken so they ordered chicken tacos and a chicken sandwich and they gave a very good review to me because they loved it.

Their food was full of flavor specially the sandwiches. It&apos;s very difficult to find a sandwich which has less flavor of the bread and more of the content inside. We loved it totally.

I am so glad that I found this Mexican place near my house and I would love to go there at any time now to have their tacos for dinner."
