Would NOT recommend the seasonal special &quot;Perfect Fall Tlayuda&quot;. It did NOT look like it&apos;s picture. Instead it was very dry and confusing. It&apos;s a wood-fired corn masa tostada with slow-cooked duck carnitas, maple-roasted butternut, kalettes, two cheeses (Jack &amp; añejo), salsa roja, black bean spread. The kalettes and butternut were very chewy (almost raw) and the whole thing was dark/ unappetizing looking due to the black bean spread."
